The paper deals with the maximization of weakly submodular functions subject to constraints, which is a problem in discrete optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm in practice, which suggests that it may belong to the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the analysis of approximation ratios, which is a topic in theoretical computer science, suggesting that it may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
